  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Lumbar disc herniation is the most important and frequent affection in rheumatology. The
      first treatment is based on an non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs.Physiotherapy also is
      used.But when there is no efficient result, it's usual to propose to the patient corticoid
      injection, percutaneous intervention or arthrodesis.

      Recently DISCOGEL® is a medical device used for lumbar disc herniation. However there is no
      studies evaluating the benefit and the efficiency of this technic. Since a few years, the
      rheumatology service of GHPSJ practise this technic using DISCOGEL® with patient resistant to
      the medical treatment . So the aim is to evaluate the benefit of DISCOGEL® retrospectively.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
